Tara (Toonimated)

09/02/2023 at 16:47:09 PDT

Thank you, Zoe, for calling out the TW on the video Julian posted yesterday. We will try to be more on top of that going forward, and we apologize to anyone who may have been negatively impacted yesterday. We're still trying to figure out how best to approach the task of warnings (especially as we share things in Discord where there's no obvious place to put it where everyone will be guaranteed to see it), and there are certain things (like mysterious suicide and mental illness) that are central elements in the story and will come up a lot, so we probably will need to just put a content warning on the whole thing up front. For now, I've created a channel called # pintv-content-warnings where I will list all of the triggers we know will come up as well as all of the ones we promise WILL NOT come up. For the record, those are: Content and Trigger warnings that WILL appear in PINTV: - mentions of suicide - descriptions of mental illness / disorders - mental health facilities - trypophobia - bugs and parasites - blood and gore - supernatural body horror Content that WILL NOT appear in PINTV: - sexual assault - pedophilia - animal abuse - graphic depictions of torture I may be forgetting some things, so I'll try to keep the list updated if something else occurs to me. Just remember that at the end of the day, the series is going to be rated Teen or PG-13 and the horror will be of a supernatural nature, so unless you have a specific trigger (in which case of course you should exercise caution and take care of your mental health as you best know how), there shouldn't be anything overtly disturbing. If for some reason something changes, we'll do our best to call it out in advance. I hope this helps, but if you have any other concerns about specific potential triggers, you can ask us in # pintv-content-warnings and we'll do our best to answer.

Dakota/

Tara (Toonimated)

11/15/2023 at 16:53:36 PST

I'm so glad! And thank you so much, everyone, for your kind words and encouragement. 💖 I think we have learned a lot since making Room of Swords and Love Me to Death, and we're excited to apply the knowledge. Not just the things we've learned about writing a story and experimental multimedia stuff, but also about gratitude and recognizing how lucky we are to have amazing fans like all of you who get excited about the same kinds of things we do. So this time we're really going to try to lean into what we love and hopefully that comes through for you guys too. We want to pack the story full of little secrets and clues that will hopefully be fun to theorize about. We are taking some risks with the story as well which we are a little nervous but also eager to see everyone's reactions to, but hopefully it will pay off and be something special and innovative for you all to sink your teeth into 🙂 Metaphorically speaking, of course. (probably.) 😁
